items.name: stripRe
items.text:
A regular expression for stripping non-numeric characters from a numeric value.
This should be overridden for localization.

items.name: AUTO
items.text: This data type means that no conversion is applied to the raw data before it is placed into a Record.

items.name: STRING
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a String before it is placed into a Record.

items.name: INT
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into an integer before it is placed into a Record. The synonym INTEGER is equivalent.

items.name: FLOAT
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a number before it is placed into a Record. The synonym NUMBER is equivalent.

items.name: BOOL
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a boolean before it is placed into a Record. The string "true" and the number 1 are converted to boolean true. The synonym BOOLEAN is equivalent.

items.name: DATE
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a Date before it is placed into a Record. The date format is specified in the constructor of the Ext.data.Field to which this type is being applied.

items.name: BOOLEAN
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a boolean before it is placed into a Record. The string "true" and the number 1 are converted to boolean `true`. The synonym BOOL is equivalent.

items.name: INTEGER
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into an integer before it is placed into a Record. The synonym INT is equivalent.

items.name: NUMBER
items.text: This data type means that the raw data is converted into a number before it is placed into a Record. The synonym FLOAT is equivalent.
